 wiki_sort1 <- wiki_hot_100s %>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  filter(year <= 2009 & year >= 2000) %>%
  group_by(artist) %>%
  summarise(nsongs = n()) %>% 
  slice_max(n = 15, order_by = nsongs) %>%

  1. Sometimes we want data from a public website that isnt provided in a file format. To obtain this data, youll need to use web scraping, and the easiest way to do this in R is with the rvest package. If we want to iterate over a span of years, using the purrr package is the least tedious and more effective way of doing so, by using functional programming concepts to iterate.
